==History==
February 1991 saw the opening of the first stores in Shinchon, Seodaemun-gu, Seoul, and Sinchon. In 2005, more than 1,000 stores across the country, the Republic of Korea is a convenience store chain. The Orion Group family, but from the original Oriental Group, Korea Retail Holdings, which was sold in 2005 and was sold again in January 2010, Lotte Eleven.<ref>[http://www.mt.co.kr/view/mtview.php?type=1&no=2008052818462991225&outlink=1 바이더웨이, 2년 만에 다시 매물 나왔지만…] - 머니투데이</ref><ref>[http://www.mt.co.kr/view/mtview.php?type=1&no=2010012518220628754&outlink=1 롯데 세븐일레븐, 바이더웨이 2750억에 인수] - 머니투데이</ref> '''Buy the Way''' were gradually incorporated into the name of the Seven-Eleven store.

