[[File:The National Archives UK - CO 1069-34-62 2 001.jpg|right|thumb|Krobo girl carrying water, late 19th century]] The '''Krobo people''' are an [[ethnic group]] in [[Ghana]]. They are grouped as part of [[Ga-Adangbe people|Ga-Adangbe]] ethnolinguistic group and they are also the largest group of the seven Dangme ethnic groups of Southeastern Ghana. The Krobo are a farming people who occupy Accra Plains, Akuapem Mountains and the [[Afram River|Afram Basin]].<ref>The Krobo People of Ghana to 1892: A Political and Social History. Louis Edward Wilson Ohio University, Center for International Studies, 1991</ref> ==Gallery== <gallery> The_National_Archives_UK_-_CO_1069-34-62_1_001.jpg|Krobo girl dressing her hair, late 19th century The National Archives UK - CO 1069-34-144-1-001.jpg|Marketplace in Krobo country, late 19th century Perle-krobo-gana.jpg|Krobo beads Pgbeads.JPG|Powdered glass Krobo beads Pgbeads2.JPG|Krobo bead made of fused glass fragments Pgbeads3.JPG|Krobo "writing" bead </gallery>
