Ndazola{{Pronunciation-needed}}  is an [[Africa|african]] [[Botswana]] traditional dance practiced by [[kalanga people]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.knowbotswana.com/botswana-dance.html|title=African Botswana dance tradition|website=know Botswana}}</ref> Ndazola is common in the northern parts of Botswana which includes [[Palapye]], [[Francistown]], [[Mathangwane]], [[Goshwe]], [[Tonota]] and others.

